  "instructions": [
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the sliced ginger and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the chicken breast and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes.",
    "Add the mustard seeds, fish sauce, sugar, and cream of tartar, and stir to combine.",
    "Pour in the water and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.",
    "Add the bean sprouts and cook for another 2-3 minutes, until they are tender.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve the chicken and broth in bowls, with lime wedges on the side."
